						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I can spot FM a mile away -- that same stale sound of an old Casio keyboard.</div><br />Yamaha keyboards are <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frequency_modulation_synthesis" class="postlink">FM synthesis</a>. Casio keyboards are <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phase_distortion_synthesis" class="postlink">phase distortion synthesis</a>, which is subtly different to get around Yamaha's patent.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Yeah I'm sure you're right.  I just look at the FDS's sound channel and imagine how they could have a 8+ channels of a more modernized version of that same concept --- it would just be <em>so</em> much nicer.</div>
<br />That would be the Virtual Boy sound chip.</div>

